┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    USER PREFERENCE FLOW                      │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

1. USER SIGNS UP
   ↓
2. ONBOARDING SCREEN: "What interests you?"
   ☐ Technology  ☐ Sports  ☐ Business
   ☐ Entertainment  ☐ Health  ☐ Science
   ↓
3. USER SELECTS: Technology, Sports
   ↓
4. SAVE TO DATABASE (user_preference table)
   ↓
5. HOME FEED SHOWS:
   - 60% Technology news
   - 30% Sports news
   - 10% Other categories (for discovery)
   ↓
6. USER CAN CHANGE ANYTIME in Settings



┌──────────────────┐         ┌──────────────────────┐
│      USER        │         │   USER_PREFERENCE    │
├──────────────────┤         ├──────────────────────┤
│ id (PK)          │◄────────│ id (PK)              │
│ email            │    1:1  │ user_id (FK)         │
│ password         │         │ category_1           │
│ full_name        │         │ category_2           │
│ created_at       │         │ category_3           │
└──────────────────┘         │ notification_enabled │
                             │ notification_time    │
                             │ language             │
                             │ updated_at           │
                             └──────────────────────┘

Why 1:1 Relationship?
- Each user has EXACTLY ONE preference record
- Easy to query and update
- Better performance than many-to-many